# app/static/

This folder contains static files served directly to the browser.

## Structure
- `css/` for stylesheets
- `js/` for client-side JavaScript
- (optional later) `img/` for images, icons, etc.

## What belongs here
- CSS files referenced by templates
- JavaScript files referenced by templates
- Images and other static assets

## What does NOT belong here
- HTML templates (those go in `app/templates/`)
- Python code (those go in `app/`)
- SQL queries (those go in `app/db/`)

## Notes
Use Flask’s `url_for("static", filename="...")` to link static files in templates.